\begin{tcbProblem}[label={problem:0020:question:Eng}]
	\( n\mathexclam \) means \( n \times \lparen n \minus 1 \rparen \times \unicodecdots \times 3 \times 2 \times 1 \)

	For example, \( 10 \mathexclam \equal 10 \times 9 \times \unicodecdots \times 3 \times 2 \times 1 \equal 3628800 \),
	and the sum of the digits in the number \( 10 \mathexclam \) is \( 3 \mathplus 6 \mathplus 2 \mathplus 8 \mathplus 8 \mathplus 0 \mathplus 0 \equal 27 \).

	Find the sum of the digits in the number \( 100 \mathexclam \)
	\par\hrefOriginalPage{20}%
\tcbline%
	\( n \times \lparen n \minus 1 \rparen \times \unicodecdots \times 3 \times 2 \times 1 \)を\( n\mathexclam \)と表す．

	例えば，
	\( 10 \mathexclam \equal 10 \times 9 \times \unicodecdots \times 3 \times 2 \times 1 \equal 3628800 \)となる．

	この数の各桁の合計は\( 3 \mathplus 6 \mathplus 2 \mathplus 8 \mathplus 8 \mathplus 0 \mathplus 0 \equal 27 \)である．

	では，\( 100\mathexclam \)の各位の数字の和を求めよ．
	\par\hrefTransitionPageJpn{20}%
\end{tcbProblem}
